-- Ex-divs to take 2.05 points off FTSE 100 on Aug 27
-- By Sudip Kar-Gupta
-- Tue Aug 26, 2014 05:45AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Aug 26 (Reuters) - The following FTSE 100 <.FTSE> companies will go ex-dividend on Wednesday, after which investors will no longer qualify for the latest dividend payout.     According to Reuters calculations at current market prices, the effect of  the resulting adjustment to prices by market-makers would take up to 2.05 points off the index.

